### Vet Connect API - HTTP Request Examples
### Use with VS Code REST Client Extension or Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@token = 

### ============================================
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Register a new owner
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "role": "OWNER"
}

### Register a new veterinarian
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "vet@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123",
  "firstName": "Dr.",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "phoneNumber": "+0987654321",
  "role": "VETERINARIAN",
  "specialization": "Small Animals",
  "licenseNumber": "VET123456"
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123"
}

### Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### ============================================
### USER ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Get current authenticated user
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get user by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### PET ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create a new pet
POST {{baseUrl}}/pets?ownerId=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Buddy",
  "species": "Dog",
  "breed": "Golden Retriever",
  "color": "Golden",
  "weight": 30.5,
  "dateOfBirth": "2020-01-15",
  "microchipNumber": "123456789",
  "medicalHistory": "Vaccinated, no known allergies",
  "vaccinations": "DHPP, Rabies"
}

### Get pet by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/pets/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all pets for owner
GET {{baseUrl}}/pets/owner/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all pets (Admin/Vet only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/pets
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update pet
PUT {{baseUrl}}/pets/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Buddy",
  "species": "Dog",
  "breed": "Golden Retriever",
  "color": "Golden",
  "weight": 31.0,
  "dateOfBirth": "2020-01-15",
  "microchipNumber": "123456789",
  "medicalHistory": "Vaccinated, no known allergies, recent checkup",
  "vaccinations": "DHPP, Rabies"
}

### Delete pet
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/pets/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### CONSULTATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create consultation
POST {{baseUrl}}/consultations?ownerId=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "petId": 1,
  "title": "Regular Checkup",
  "description": "Annual health checkup",
  "symptoms": "No symptoms",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "consultationDate": "2026-03-10T14:00:00"
}

### Get consultation by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/consultations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get consultations for owner
GET {{baseUrl}}/consultations/owner/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get consultations for veterinarian
GET {{baseUrl}}/consultations/veterinarian/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get consultations for pet
GET {{baseUrl}}/consultations/pet/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all consultations (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/consultations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update consultation
PUT {{baseUrl}}/consultations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "petId": 1,
  "title": "Regular Checkup",
  "description": "Annual health checkup completed",
  "symptoms": "No symptoms",
  "diagnosis": "Healthy, no issues found",
  "notes": "Dog is in excellent health",
  "status": "COMPLETED",
  "veterinarianId": 2
}

### Assign veterinarian to consultation
PUT {{baseUrl}}/consultations/1/assign-veterinarian/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Rate consultation
PUT {{baseUrl}}/consultations/1/rate?rating=5&feedback=Excellent service
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Delete consultation
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/consultations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### PRESCRIPTION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create prescription
POST {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "consultationId": 1,
  "petId": 1,
  "veterinarianId": 2,
  "medicationName": "Amoxicillin",
  "dosage": "250 mg",
  "frequency": "twice daily",
  "duration": 7,
  "instructions": "Take with food",
  "sideEffects": "May cause upset stomach",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "prescribedDate": "2026-03-05",
  "startDate": "2026-03-05",
  "endDate": "2026-03-12"
}

### Get prescription by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get prescriptions for consultation
GET {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/consultation/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get prescriptions for pet
GET {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/pet/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get prescriptions for veterinarian
GET {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/veterinarian/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all prescriptions (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update prescription
PUT {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "consultationId": 1,
  "petId": 1,
  "veterinarianId": 2,
  "medicationName": "Amoxicillin",
  "dosage": "250 mg",
  "frequency": "twice daily",
  "duration": 7,
  "instructions": "Take with food after meals",
  "sideEffects": "May cause upset stomach",
  "status": "COMPLETED",
  "prescribedDate": "2026-03-05",
  "startDate": "2026-03-05",
  "endDate": "2026-03-12",
  "notes": "Patient responded well to treatment"
}

### Delete prescription
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/prescriptions/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
### ============================================

### For VS Code REST Client:
### 1. Install "REST Client" extension
### 2. Update @baseUrl with your API endpoint
### 3. Click "Send Request" above each endpoint
### 4. Save token from login response and update @token

### For Postman:
### 1. Create new Collection
### 2. Create requests from examples above
### 3. Use {{baseUrl}} and {{token}} as variables
### 4. Save responses for reuse

### Note: Replace all IDs (1, 2, etc.) with actual IDs from your system
